reviewText: In the vein of Tennessee Williams, Stanley Bennett Clay's Ritual is an exercise in character study. The Becker clan are characters on the brink. The parents and their offspring in this film are flawed, filled with emotion, and locked in the frustration of straining for something beyond reach. The impending doom for the Becker family seeps into your lungs like dust from a room that hasn't been cleaned in decades. SBC had a distinct and defined vision for his plays and the style in which he wanted to present them. Shawn Michael Howard is restrained in his portrayal of Mason. Denise Nicholas is well aware of her surroundings as Sylvia but is impotent when it comes to her daughter Angelle Brooks' Terri.
